tton><div class=3D"content-container xl:px-0 bg-white"><div class=3D"w-full=
 overflow-hidden"><h2 class=3D"mb-6">Best practices for reporting p-values =
in research</h2><div class=3D"PortableText_page-builder__oGx0w guide-body l=
ong-form-rich-text"><p>Providing a complete and transparent picture of your=
 experimental results improves the credibility of your findings, leading to=
 better decision-making in your <a href=3D"https://amplitude.com/explore/pr=
oduct/product-development-process" class=3D"btn-text" aria-label=3D"product=
 development ">product development </a>process. Accurate reporting means mo=
re trustworthy research that benefits your entire business.</p><p>Following=
 these best practices will help ensure clarity and preciseness.</p><h3 id=
=3D"report-exact-p-values">Report exact p-values</h3><p>Instead of just say=
ing =E2=80=9Cp &lt; 0.05=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CP &gt; 0.05=E2=80=9D, provide=
 more information by providing the actual p-value (e.g., p =3D 0.032).</p><=
p>Readers can use this data to interpret the strength of the evidence for t=
hemselves and compare the results across different experiments.</p><h3 id=
=3D"provide-context">Provide context</h3><p>Always report p-values alongsid=
e effect sizes and confidence intervals. For example, you might say, =E2=80=
=9CThe new checkout process increased conversion rates by 2.5 percentage po=
ints (95% CI: 1.2 to 3.8 percentage points, p =3D 0.001).=E2=80=9D</p><p>Th=
is context provides a more complete and more precise picture of your result=
s.</p><h3 id=3D"pre-specify-your-threshold">Pre-specify your threshold</h3>=
<p>Before running your experiment, decide on and clearly state your signifi=
cance level (e.g., a =3D 0.05). Significance levels prevent the temptation =
to move the goalposts after seeing the results.</p><h3 id=3D"be-transparent=
">Be transparent</h3><p>Report how all the tests performed, even those that=
 weren=E2=80=99t significant. Being more open with your results helps comba=
t publication bias and p-hacking.</p><h3 id=3D"avoid-loaded-language">Avoid=
 loaded language</h3><p>Terms like =E2=80=9Chighly significant=E2=80=9D or =
=E2=80=9Cmarginally significant=E2=80=9D can mislead. Let the numbers speak=
 for themselves.</p><h3 id=3D"discuss-practical-significance">Discuss pract=
ical significance</h3><p>Go beyond statistical significance to explain what=
 your results mean in real-world terms for your product=E2=80=94even =E2=80=
=98positive=E2=80=99 changes may not provide enough uplift to implement ful=
ly.</p><p>For instance: =E2=80=9CWhile the new email subject line significa=
ntly increased open rates (p =3D 0.04), the absolute increase was only 0.5 =
percentage points, translating to about 50 additional opens per campaign. G=
iven the effort required to implement this change, we don=E2=80=99t conside=
r this practically significant.=E2=80=9D</p><h3 id=3D"interpret-cautiously"=
>Interpret cautiously</h3><p>Discuss p-values in context to consider limita=
tions and alternative explanations. Did you run the test during a major hol=
iday or broader product update? Acknowledge how events like these might hav=
e influenced your results, and mention them in your reports to avoid overst=
ating your conclusions.</p><h3 id=3D"use-visualizations">Use visualizations=
</h3><p>Graphs, charts, and other <a href=3D"https://amplitude.com/explore/=
data/data-visualization" class=3D"btn-text" aria-label=3D"data visualizatio=
ns">data visualizations</a> communicate your results more clearly than p-va=
lues alone.</p><p>You might include a <a href=3D"https://www.sciencedirect.=
com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/forest-plot" class=3D"btn-text" aria-labe=
l=3D"forest plot">forest plot</a> showing effect sizes and confidence inter=
vals for different variations tests or a cumulative <a href=3D"https://www.=
itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/eda/section3/probplot.htm" class=3D"btn-text" =
aria-label=3D"probability plot">probability plot</a> showing how the p-valu=
e evolved throughout your experiment.</p></div></div></div></div></div></di=
v></div><div data-toc-section-key=3D"32bd7ca2dcff"><div><div class=3D"relat=
ive max-h-0" style=3D"top: -132px;"><button class=3D"absolute max-h-0" id=
